What are the main components of Splunk architecture?

| Component               | Purpose                                                                  |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Universal Forwarder** | Lightweight agent that collects and forwards logs to indexers.           |
| **Indexer**             | Parses and stores the data into indexes; responsible for fast searching. |
| **Search Head**         | Provides a UI for users to search, create dashboards, alerts, etc.       |
| **Deployment Server**   | Manages configurations for multiple forwarders (mostly in large setups). |
| **Cluster Master**      | Coordinates indexing and search operations in clustered environments.    |
